fields.description:
Received the following error while trying to add AWS CodeDeploy to Individual account

{code}
#!python

The add-on failed to be installed: Error calling installed at URL https://codedeploy.bitbucketconnect.com/addon_installation_callback: 500 Server Error: Internal Server Error for url: https://codedeploy.bitbucketconnect.com/addon_installation_callback

{code}

The slack integration doesn’t resolve the username,  instead it shows as a url with uuid.

for example

Comment from [https://bitbucket.org/|https://bitbucket.org/%257B6f5ea5f1-c84a-4ab3-8ee3-f70f98b7d71c%257D/]{some_uuid_represent_the name}

previous it display as

Comment from {Actual User Name}

Previous (correct) header:

{code}
From: "Forename Surname" <issues-reply@bitbucket.org>
{code}

We now see two nonsense versions for this header (this randomly differs for each email):

{code}
From: ForenameSurname@bitbucket.org
From: Forename@bitbucket.org, Surname@bitbucket.org
{code}

Could you please fix this.

According to [this|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucketserver/markdown-syntax-guide-776639995.html] you support the common-mark spec. However, from [this snippet|https://bitbucket.org/snippets/yehmixela/qeGnbn] it looks like backslashes don’t work for [hard line breaks|https://spec.commonmark.org/0.29/#hard-line-breaks].

This should render with a hard break.

{code}
hello\
world
{code}

I am using the following endpoint as per the documentation https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/{team-name}/{repo-slug}/deploy-keys/{id} but I get the following 404 error.

{code:json}
{
    "type": "error",
    "error": {
        "message": "No DeployKey matches the given query."
    }
}
{code}

I am able to delete the deployment key using the Bitbucket 1.0 API. The 2.0 API is not working as per the documentation. This has a major impact in our deployment process. Since the 1.0 API are going to be deprecated soon could you please add the key deletion support in 2.0 as soon as possible.

Currently, when you use the API diff endpoint with a huge amount of data response, the result of the API call is "Unable to respond in time".

*Endpoint:*

{code}
#!curl

CURL -sL -u username:password https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/username/repo_name/diff/username/repo_name:523a7ec383dc%0D637f6b25edf5?from_pullrequest_id=1&context=0
{code}

*Result:*

{code}
#!python

{
  "type": "error",
  "error": {
    "message": "Unable to respond in time"
  }
}
{code}

https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/resource/repositories/%7Busername%7D/%7Brepo_slug%7D/diff/%7Bspec%7D

It would be best if we could allow large return data for the Git diff API.
